<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14074">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Climbing.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12783">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12783 mb-requirement-id-12784">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the most likely hazards you may encounter
        while participating in climbing and rappelling activities and what you
        should do to anticipate, help prevent, mitigate, and respond to these
        hazards. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/7YqZkQRSMRw" target="_blank"
          >Risk Management in Rock Climbing (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12783 mb-requirement-id-12785">
        (b) Show that you know first aid for and how to prevent injuries or
        illnesses that could occur during climbing activities, including heat
        and cold reactions, dehydration, stopped breathing, sprains, abrasions,
        fractures, rope burns, blisters, snakebite, concussions, and insect
        bites or stings. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/rope-burn" target="_blank"
          >Treatment of Rope Burns (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/x-YYjkokQ6U" target="_blank"
          >Head, Neck, and Spine Injuries (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/mlWaByoT24s" target="_blank"
          >First Aid for Concussions (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/sPzXAVNVJr0" target="_blank"
          >Fracture and Dislocation (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/tGqXa3wujiM" target="_blank"
          >How To Treat A Blister Correctly (First, Look At Your Blister Roof)
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/KahsIEbFROI" target="_blank"
          >What Is Dehydration? Causes, Signs and Symptoms, Diagnosis and
          Treatment. (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12783 mb-requirement-id-12786">
        (c) Identify the conditions that must exist before performing CPR on a
        person. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/khJ40b2TuHg" target="_blank"
          >What To Do Before Starting Hands-Only CPR (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12795">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Learn the Leave No Trace Seven Principles and the Outdoor Code and explain
      what they mean. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a
        href="https://vimeo.com/1115216743/63b20c0b33?share=copy"
        target="_blank"
        >Leave No Trace (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12796">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Present yourself properly dressed for belaying, climbing, and rappelling.
      Explain why you are wearing each piece of gear and discuss qualities of
      easy movement, entanglement free and good weather protection and comfort.
      <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/xBS6SxlC64s" target="_blank"
        >Sport Climbing Gear Checklist (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/jBa5TuXjHOE" target="_blank"
        >How To Choose Climbing Shoes (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/llSukbWw5kQ" target="_blank"
        >How To Pick Top 10 Sport Climbing Essentials (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://www.rei.com/dam/sport_climbing_checklist.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >Sport Climbing Gear Checklist (PDF)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/KpxCQgL5oZw" target="_blank"
        >What Gear Do You Need for Winter Climbing (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12757">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      <strong>Location.</strong> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12757 mb-requirement-id-12758">
        (a) Explain how the difficulty of climbs is classified, and apply
        classifications to the rock faces or walls where you will demonstrate
        your climbing skills. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/cD4XHKBwe3I" target="_blank"
          >Climbing Grades Explained (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12757 mb-requirement-id-12759">
        (b) Explain the following: top-rope climbing, lead climbing, and
        bouldering. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/1Wri-kqrX80" target="_blank"
          >Top Roping vs Lead Climbing vs Bouldering (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12757 mb-requirement-id-12760">
        (c) Evaluate the safety of a particular climbing area. Consider weather,
        visibility, the condition of the climbing surface, and any other
        environmental hazards.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12757 mb-requirement-id-12761">
        (d) Determine how to summon aid to the climbing area in case of an
        emergency. Discuss what medical training is needed for your group when
        climbing and rappelling in remote areas.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12762">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      <strong>Verbal signals.</strong> Explain the importance of using verbal
      signals during every climb and rappel, and while bouldering. With the help
      of the counselor or another Scout, demonstrate the verbal signals used by
      each of the following: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a
        href="https://americanalpineclub.org/news/2017/1/19/4xm1fcsag6b7xqf1p1w1qp7vdpp1ha"
        target="_blank"
        >Climber Communication (website)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12762 mb-requirement-id-12763">
        (a) Climbers <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/gxfGI0AGEMA" target="_blank"
          >Rock Climbing Commands (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12762 mb-requirement-id-12764">
        (b) Rappellers
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12762 mb-requirement-id-12765">
        (c) Belayers <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/GRLUYDGHIEI" target="_blank"
          >Gym Top Rope Climbing: Verbal Commands (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Ilmv4bsWSXcr" target="_blank"
          >SL Climb Series: Rock Climbers Communicate How? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12762 mb-requirement-id-12766">
        (d) Boulderers and their spotters <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YZbzT5ijJd8" target="_blank"
          >ABCDs of Spotting (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12767">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      <strong>Rope.</strong> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12767 mb-requirement-id-12768">
        (a) Describe the kinds of rope acceptable for use in climbing and
        rappelling. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/1AxF_0S7BTY" target="_blank"
          >The Essential Guide for Every Climber (Dynamic vs Static Ropes)
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12767 mb-requirement-id-12769">
        (b) Show how to examine a rope for signs of wear or damage. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/p3xFDP9G0ow" target="_blank"
          >Rope Inspection 101: One of the Most Important Safety Steps
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12767 mb-requirement-id-12770">
        (c) Discuss ways to prevent a rope from being damaged. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.namahropes.com/rope-safety-tips-for-reliable-use/"
          target="_blank"
          >Safety First: Preventing Rope Failures and Ensuring Longevity
          (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12767 mb-requirement-id-12771">
        (d) Explain when and how a rope should be retired. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/0MD83ewJFMA" target="_blank"
          >When To Retire a Climbing Rope (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12767 mb-requirement-id-12772">
        (e) Properly coil a rope. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Aqt1ntSVjJA" target="_blank"
          >How To Coil a Climbing Rope (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12773">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      <strong>Knots.</strong> Demonstrate the ability to tie each of the
      following knots. Give at least one example of how each knot is used in
      belaying, climbing, or rappelling.
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12773 mb-requirement-id-12774">
        (a) Figure eight on a bight <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/kbB85p_uJsE" target="_blank"
          >How To Tie a Figure 8 Knot on a Bight (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12773 mb-requirement-id-12775">
        (b) Figure eight follow-through <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/GFlwrvggas0" target="_blank"
          >How To Tie a Figure 8 Knot for Climbing - Everything You Need To Know
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12773 mb-requirement-id-12776">
        (c) Water knot <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/mWKfGmA3M48" target="_blank"
          >Rock Climbing: How To Tie a Water Knot (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12773 mb-requirement-id-12777">
        (d) Double fisherman's knot (grapevine knot) <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/iZuqOkTumSQ" target="_blank"
          >How To Tie a Double Fisherman's Knot (Grapevine Knot) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YHUv-oOMwRA" target="_blank"
          >Rock Climbing: How To Tie a Double Fisherman's Knot (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12773 mb-requirement-id-12778">
        (e) Prusik hitch applied to rope <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/EFHxQ5fiUvI" target="_blank"
          >Rock Climbing: How To Tie a Prusik Knot (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12797">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      <b>Harness, Helmet &amp; Gloves.</b> Explain the purpose of each of the
      following and demonstrate how to put them on correctly.
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12797 mb-requirement-id-12799">
        (a) Commercially made climbing harness <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/aRrLfR7rnw0" target="_blank"
          >How to Choose a Climbing Harness (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/v5WpeMStpf0" target="_blank"
          >How To Put On a Climbing Harness (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12797 mb-requirement-id-12800">
        (b) Climbing helmet <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/NFzGftaJOvM" target="_blank"
          >How To Choose Climbing Helmets (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12797 mb-requirement-id-12801">
        (c) Climbing or rappelling gloves <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.gearinstant.com/things-you-should-know-before-choosing-gloves-for-climbing"
          target="_blank"
          >Things You Should Know Before Choosing Gloves for Climbing
          (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12802">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      Identify the elements of the CHECK system and describe the meaning of each
      one to your counselor. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/5YC-t0cwVr0" target="_blank"
        >Climbing Partner Checks—Check or Deck (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12779">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 10. </span>
      <strong>Belaying.</strong> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12779 mb-requirement-id-12780">
        (a) Explain the importance of belaying climbers and rappellers and when
        it is necessary. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/CFIz4cBFVro" target="_blank"
          >How To Top-Rope Belay (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12779 mb-requirement-id-12781">
        (b) Belay three different climbers on three different routes.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12779 mb-requirement-id-12782">
        (c) Serve as a backup belayer on three different climbs. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Uuv1B-C1Ziw" target="_blank"
          >How To Back Up a Beginner's Belay (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12779 mb-requirement-id-12803">
        (d) Belay three different rappellers on three different routes.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12779 mb-requirement-id-12804">
        (e) Serve as a backup belayer on three different rappels.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12787">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 11. </span>
      <strong>Climbing.</strong> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12787 mb-requirement-id-12788">
        (a) Show the correct way to directly tie a belay rope to your harness.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/XQ1r7iddc1w" target="_blank"
          >How To Tie Into a Climbing Harness (With a Figure 8 Knot) (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12787 mb-requirement-id-12789">
        (b) Climb at least three different routes on a rock face or climbing
        wall, demonstrating good technique and using verbal signals with a
        belayer.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12790">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 12. </span>
      <strong>Rappelling.</strong> Do the following: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/7U6tdEevJgs" target="_blank"
        >Rock Climbing: How to Rappel (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12790 mb-requirement-id-12791">
        (a) Show the correct way to directly tie a belay rope to your harness.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12790 mb-requirement-id-12792">
        (b) Using a carabiner and a rappel device, attach a rappel rope to your
        harness.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12790 mb-requirement-id-12793">
        (c) Rappel down three different rock faces or three rappel routes on a
        climbing wall. Use verbal signals to communicate with a belayer, and
        demonstrate good rappelling technique.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12794">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 13. </span>
      Demonstrate ways to store rope, hardware, and other gear used for
      climbing, rappelling, and belaying.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
